1.title: Austin Couple Finds Waco Charm
1.plot: Matt and Samanatha Hardy are looking to move from Austin to Waco, Texas and buy their first house together.

2.title: Family Seeks Spacious Upgrade
2.plot: Bryce and Emily Sandvall want a new home for their family of five in the Woodward area that's not only right for their family but also has a traditional design style that they love.

3.title: New Chapter for Family of Four
3.plot: After looking at houses for months with no luck, Gayle and Tim Jackson need help to find a new place for their family of four that has four bedrooms and three bathrooms that, ideally, can be renovated within their budget.

4.title: Historic Tudor Style Home for a New Family
4.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines take on a project for a couple ready to upgrade from a loft to a house in which to raise their new baby. Built in 1927, their Tudor-style home has little functionality and lacks a true master suite.

5.title: Ranch House to Modern Mediterranean Retreat
5.plot: Chip and Joanna work with the Aguilar family to find a forever home that their family of four and reflects their personal style.

6.title: Flip House To Family Project
6.plot: Chip and Joanna return to their roots and give a home a clean, new look, until Jo decides she wants her sister and brother-in-law to buy the house. They modify the design plans in hopes it will persuade them to buy it.

7.title: New Chapter, New House
7.plot: Chip and Jo meet with a client who just purchased a 1950s bungalow hoping to make it her forever home after losing her husband to cancer.

8.title: A Classic, Traditional Beauty
8.plot: Chip and Jo turn a family's bland, outdated home into a dazzling dwelling full of classic charm and traditional beauty.

9.title: A Modern Cabin Makeover
9.plot: Chip and Jo team up with their friend Jimmy Don Holmes to transform a bland little house into a modern mountain cabin for his son. Former first lady Laura Bush stops by to help with a heartfelt finishing touch.

10.title: Touchdown for a Family in Need
10.plot: Chip and Joanna team up with Tim Tebow and his foundation to create a wheelchair accessible home for the Copp Family.

11.title: Big Budget for a Big House
11.plot: Chip and Jo transform a house into a French country-meets-tradit ional style retreat for a family of five.

12.title: Chip and Jo's Family Garden Project
12.plot: The Gaines family builds a cottage-style garden that includes a chicken coop and a one-of-a-kind garden shed.

13.title: A European Cottage-Style Dream Home with a View
13.plot: Chip and Jo take on a renovation for clients looking for a European cottage-style with a view.

14.title: All-American Farmhouse
14.plot: Chip and Jo are called to convert a wounded veteran's barn into a dreamy farmhouse. But with a meager all-in budget, Chip and Jo decide to reach out to the community to raise additional funds to cover the costs of the renovation.

15.title: A Downtown Loft Challenge for Chip and Jo
15.plot: Chip and Jo meet up with a friend who is hoping to buy a modern industrial-style loft apartment in downtown Waco. After finding the perfect spot, they get to work tackling their first-ever downtown loft apartment.

16.title: From City Life in Pakistan to a Farmhouse in Waco
16.plot: After 17 years of working and living abroad in Pakistan, a couple returns home to Waco and enlists Chip and Jo to help renovate an 1890's farmhouse they bought sight unseen.

17.title: Chip and Jo's Breakfast Joint
17.plot: Chip Gaines has always dreamed of opening a restaurant. After Jo walks the Elite Cafe property that's for sale and hears his vision for a modern breakfast joint, she jumps on board and agrees to help make Chip's dream a reality.

18.title: Rock Star Renovation
18.plot: Musician Mike Herrera and his wife, Holli, are moving to Waco and want a home with lots of space and a large studio. But when Chip finds serious structural issues, they realize they may not finish the project in time.

1.title: Looking Old But Feeling New
1.plot: Joanna and Chip help a couple find the diamond in the rough in a neighborhood known for mansions.

2.title: Young Family Takes on History
2.plot: Joanna and Chip Gaines introduce clients Charmaine and Chuck to the historic Sanger Heights neighborhood. The family wants to be a part of the revitalization of this community of homes that are either vacant or dilapidated.

3.title: Nomad Family Seeks Final Home
3.plot: Chip and Jo Gaines take Becky and Heath Ivy to Woodway, TX in search of a home for their growing family and Heath's thriving business. They tour three houses with three different styles and three unique construction challenges.

4.title: Client Rebuilds After Tragedy
4.plot: Carolyn Muska is rebuilding her life after losing her West, TX, home and her husband to a devastating fertilizer plant explosion that killed 15 and leveled many homes. The Gaines show Carolyn 3 fixer uppers in her hometown of West

5.title: French Country Sought in Waco
5.plot: Dr. Jeff Sanders, wife Michelle and their two teens are a fun active family who enjoy entertaining, adventure, and travel. They want to downsize to a casual country home that offers European flair with easy access to Lake Waco.

6.title: Craftsmen Crave Urban Feel
6.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines take a tour with clients Clint and Kelly Harp through the Brook Oaks neighborhood. The Harps are big city transplants looking for a house with an urban feel.

7.title: Texan Family Returns to Roots
7.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines are excited to return to Texas after leaving Oklahoma. They look at 3 homes with John and Margie Bowman in the McGregor neighborhood just outside of Waco. They want some Texas flair that's not too 'buckaroo'

8.title: New Home New Life for Mom
8.plot: Chip and Jo take a tour with single mom Karla Griffis through the Castle Crest neighborhood of Waco, Texas. After a difficult divorce, Karla's ready to move on from the hardest time of her life to the happiest.

9.title: Missionaries Retreat in Waco
9.plot: Heather, Andrew and Steven McCall ask the Gaines to find a retreat for their missionary parents. Dr. Tim and Janice McCall run an orphanage in Uganda, living in a 160-sq-ft home. They need a refuge for their biannual visits.

10.title: Couple Reach for Unreachable
10.plot: Rachel and Andrew Erwin are asking Chip and Jo Gaines to find them a home in the Viking Hills neighborhood where 'for sale' signs are rare. But the Gaines are determined to find the young family their dream home.

11.title: Physicians Seek Farmhouse
11.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines are in Robinson, Texas, looking for a farmhouse for clients Rebecca and Joel Mahan. The couple are physicians with three kids of their own and more on the way as they plan to adopt several foster children.

12.title: Academics Seek Acreage
12.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines seek a home in Waco for Devon and Hannah Jonklaas. The Jonklaases want a home with lots of acreage and lots of bedrooms. Devon, a biochem professor, wants to be close to work and to Hannah, who's expecting.

13.title: Baby Boomers Buy Fixer Upper
13.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines are helping client Dr. Marla Hendricks find a home in Waco for her and her new husband. These baby boomers fell in love later in life but are young at heart seeking a home that will fit their lifestyle.

1.title: Newlyweds Seek First Home
1.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines take clients Kimberly and Blake Batson on a tour through three houses in Waco, TX. The young newlyweds run the 'Common Grounds' coffee shop and are looking for a home close to their business.

2.title: Young Couple Chooses Old Home
2.plot: First time buyers fall in love with a charming historic home and then face pricey repairs.

3.title: Homebuilders Seek Fixer Upper
3.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines take Genny and Russ Davis on a tour through three homes in Woodway, Texas. A desirable, established neighborhood tempts a new home builders to consider a fixer upper.

4.title: Extra Space for Blended Family
4.plot: Nearly empty nesters and boomer newlyweds search for a waterfront home for three, but with extra space when all the kids come home for their blended family of nine.

5.title: Expectant Couple Seeks Nest
5.plot: Deanna and Paul King need a bigger home for their large family. They hope to find a rural home located a reasonable distance from next door neighbors in Hubbard, Texas. Chip and Joanna show them three houses in the small town.

6.title: High School Friend Seeks Fixer Upper
6.plot: A long-time friend of Jo's returns to Waco hoping to find the perfect fixer-upper for his family.

7.title: Sports Chaplain Tackles Fixer
7.plot: A couple with conflicting taste compromises on a fixer-upper for their family.

8.title: New Homebuyers Prefer Fixer
8.plot: ....in Older Neighborhood. Join Chip and Joanne as they show first time home buyers, Brandon and Kristen Haire, homes in the established Western Hills neighborhood of Waco.

9.title: Couple Seeks a Unique Fixer
9.plot: Couple, Josh and Jill Barrett tour three houses in the Wooded Acres neighborhood that can accommodate four children, and a baby on the way. Watch as Joanna surprises Chip on his big 4-0 birthday.

10.title: Three Generations, One Fixer
10.plot: A young mother searches for a fixer with wide-open spaces and room to share with her mom and son.

11.title: Country Couple Seeks Fixer
11.plot: A couple who likes small towns searches Hubbard, Texas for a large home.

12.title: Island Family Seeks Space
12.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines help a family find a spacious fixer upper for lakeside fun.

13.title: Family Fancies French Flair
13.plot: An attorney and his realtor wife, search for a sizable fixer upper for their young family.

1.title: Finding Small Town Texas Charm for a Young Family
1.plot: The Dansby family currently lives in Hillsboro, TX, but their house is too small for their three growing sons. Chip and Jo found three houses that might provide the Dansbys with the space and character they're looking for.

2.title: School Spirit Spurs Home Search
2.plot: Baylor alumni Lori and Baron live in Houston, but want to purchase a second home in Waco with the hope that their 12-year-old son will continue the family's legacy. They are looking for a house full of character, but on budget.

3.title: A Family Searches a Small Town for the Ultimate Open Space
3.plot: The McKenzies want a new place close to their church, the kids' schools and a grocery store. Chip and Joanna Gaines help them find a promising house with an open concept and plenty of room for their three kids to play.

4.title: A Home Away from Home for the Holidays
4.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines turn an old Victorian beauty into a bed and breakfast just in time for the holidays.

5.title: Convenience and Character Are on the Wish List for a House Hunting Waco Couple
5.plot: The McKenzies want a new place close to their church, the kids' schools and a grocery store. Chip and Joanna Gaines help them find a promising house with an open concept and plenty of room for their three kids to play.

6.title: A One-of-a-Kind Fixer Upper Gets a Modern Makeover
6.plot: The Meeks are hoping to find a home on several acres of land so they can raise their kids in the spirit of country living. Will Chip and Jo surprise them with an outside-the-box rural renovation?

7.title: Making New Family Memories in Rural Texas
7.plot: Sterling and Casey inherited a 2,000-acre ranch with a house that has been abandoned for ten years. They hope Chip and Joanna can restore the house to its former glory.

8.title: A Young Couple Hopes for a House with Old World Charm
8.plot: Newlyweds returns to Waco, TX, to find their first home together.

9.title: Lackluster Fixer Changes to Contemporary Charm for Young Family
9.plot: A young couple with a baby girl is looking for a family-sized house with 3-4 bedrooms and a playroom/home office. With Chip and Johanna, they tour three homes near Waco, TX, and take one from lackluster to charming.

10.title: Most Eligible Bachelor Finds the Perfect Home for Entertaining
10.plot: Chip and Jo are looking for a property for David Ridley, one of Waco's most eligible bachelors. They find him a spacious lakeside home and transform it into a modern ranch.

11.title: Parents of College Students Find Fixer Close to Campus
11.plot: A California couple wants a charming fixer-upper in Waco to be near their kids at Baylor. They are looking for a three-bedroom, two-bath house full of original detailing and shiplap for under $175,000.

12.title: Newlyweds Take on a Run-Down Fixer for Their Future Together
12.plot: Chip and Joanna customize a run-down fixer-upper for newlyweds in Waco.

13.title: Chip and Jo Bring a Relaxing Coastal Feel to a Rural Fixer
13.plot: Chip and Joanna convert a rural ranch to a breezy beach-style home.

14.title: Chip and Jo Give a Run-Down Tiny House a Total Makeover for an Adventurous, Young Couple
14.plot: Cameron and Jessie love the cozy charm of small-scale living, but want a place of their own. Chip and Joanna turn an abandoned tiny house into a modern living space for the adventurous couple.

15.title: Single Foster Mom Finds Fixer for Future Family
15.plot: Chip and Jo create a charming, kid-friendly home for a single foster mom.

16.title: Family Leaves the Bustling City for Quiet Simplicity
16.plot: Chip and Jo add timeless charm to a 1950s home for a young family in Waco.

17.title: A Host & Hostess for the Bed & Breakfast
17.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

18.title: A Home for Hospitality
18.plot: Chip & Jo renovate the innkeepers' house for the Magnolia House managers.

1.title: A Dog-Loving Couple Searches for Their First Home
1.plot: Andrew and Brittany Chapman are looking to buy their first home together with plenty of space for their two dogs. Chip and Joanna have big plans for the renovation and an even bigger surprise for the Chapman's pooches.

2.title: After Recent Adoption, Family Finds Space to Thrive
2.plot: Keith and Annabeth Morgan recently adopted two girls and are hoping to find a house where their family can have space to grow. The Gaines family has a bedroom design face-off to create a special space for the Morgan kids.

3.title: Bright, Open Design Transforms Couple's First Home Together
3.plot: Matt and Melissa Yielding are looking to establish "Deeper Roots" in Waco. They end up taking a drab house and brightening it up.

4.title: Retiring to the Country
4.plot: John and Stephanie are ready to downsize as they enter retirement. After touring different homes with Chip and Jo, the couple narrows their search to two choices. However, one home is in need of major renovations.

5.title: A Veteran Home Makeover
5.plot: Chip and Joanna join Cleveland Browns quarterback and former Baylor Heisman winner, Robert Griffin III, and the US Army to give a deserving Vietnam veteran a home makeover.

6.title: Traditional Goes Ultra Modern
6.plot: A couple relocate from Denver to Texas. Chip and Joanna help them find a modern home with acreage.

7.title: Son Surprises His Family with a Major Renovation
7.plot: NFL player Kelvin Beachum's empty-nest parents want a home to accommodate their children and grandchildren. Kelvin pitches in for them to get their dream home.

8.title: Stately in White: From '80s to Elegant
8.plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines face the challenge of designing a complete home makeover for friend and fellow designer, Kristen. She's expecting a baby, so the pressure is on to create a living space that is move-in ready in two months.

9.title: The Floating Fixer Upper
9.plot: Nautical theme with Chip commissioning a custom canoe for the family. Chip & JoAnna tackle a houseboat for Waco friend Brett Swartz.

10.title: Sweet Surprise at the Silos
10.plot: Joanna wants to revive an old dream of opening a bakery by restoring the historic charm of a vacant flower shop on the corner of the Silos property. Will Chip and Jo be able to pull off their first commercial renovation?

11.title: Space in the Suburbs
11.plot: San Diego transplants Mary and Dustyn are on the hunt for their family's dream home in Waco, Texas, and they turn to Chip and Joanna to locate and renovate a four-bedroom with a large yard and open space for hosting guests.

12.title: Tight Budgets and Big Dreams
12.plot: Will and Lauren return to Waco, Texas, to raise their two daughters in the house of their dreams. They recruit Chip and Joanna to create their dream home and make their modest budget stretch to meet their expensive wish list.

14.title: Second Chance at a Country Home
14.plot: After years of living near downtown Waco, Texas, Jordan and Rachel dream of moving to the country with their three children, and they enlist the help of Chip and Joanna to get the country home they envision.

15.title: Rustic Italian Dream Home
15.plot: Jenny and Ramil are moving to Waco, Texas, from California to be closer to Ramil's mother, and they've enlisted the help of Chip and Joanna to create the rustic Italian-style dream home they crave.

17.title: The Flipper Upper
17.plot: Chip and Jo compete against each other to determine their next "flip-house." They re-visit their old house; from when Drake was born, and it brings back charming memories. (Giraffe House) vs. (Partially remodeled House )

18.title: The Colossal Crawford Reno
18.plot: A couple finds a house that's anything but a dream home in Crawford, TX. They hope Chip and Joanna can work their magic on it, but it's going to need total overhaul, making it one of the Gaines' biggest transformations ever.

-1.title: How We Got to Here: Looking Back on Fixer Upper
-1.plot: Chip and Joanna take a trip down memory lane revisiting some of their favorite renovations and design styles over the last five seasons of Fixer Upper.

imdb.title: Fixer Upper
plot: Chip and Joanna Gaines take on clients in the Waco Texas area, turning their fixer uppers into the homes of their dreams.::Heather Staake
